Question: What improvements would you like to see in these cultural funding programs?

Response ID: resp_822
Response Text: I would like to see organizations that have HAVE A HISTORY of prioritizing diversity in their artists and programs be valued as much or more than brand new organizations or organizations that have made sudden changes.  I would like to see a more wholistic and nuanced view of what diversity means.  A focus on racial diversity has always been important to me and to our organization, but WOMEN, LGBTQ, AND DISABLED ARTISTS MATTER TOO.  It seems as thought organizations that are actually diverse and have been for years are being denied funding to support organizations that are segregated by race.  I understand the noble impulse behind this move, but it has not been well-implemented and has only hurt the arts community as a whole.  I would also like to see artistic quality in programming re-enter the funding system as a priority.  Of course, the arts are subjective, but critical reviews, local awards, and audience testimony can be ways to demonstrate the artistic merit of programs.

